      "comment_id" : 89213563,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body" : "Would also like to know? Every time you need run jobs with an undefined scope / length you run the risk of dropping the job halfway through, which is mostly a dealbreaker.. Spinning up a batch job easily takes 1 to 5 minutes to fire, also not ideal.. Breaking the job up in micro jobs over Lambda makes keeping log of job status / success more complicated. Feels like the 5 minute limit is really blocking a lot of use cases, intentionally."
